## Why This Is Asked
Tests real-world CSS skills: grid complexity, responsive layouts, animation, and accessibility.

## Key Concepts
- CSS Grid responsive layouts
- Centered featured element via grid-column/grid-row
- Hover lift plus reduced-motion
- Keyboard navigation in a grid

## Code Example
```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('.card').forEach((el, idx, arr) => {
  el.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    const cols = 4;
    const delta = {ArrowLeft:-1, ArrowRight:1, ArrowUp:-cols, ArrowDown:cols}[e.key];
    if (delta !== undefined) {
      const next = arr[(idx + delta + arr.length) % arr.length];
      next.focus();
    }
  });
  el.setAttribute('tabindex','0');
});
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you adapt this for dynamic content changes (infinite loading) while preserving focus order?
- How would you audit performance and ensure 60fps during reflow?

