## Solution Overview
Use closure to encapsulate rate limiter state with request queue and timer-based enforcement.

## Key Components
- Queue array for pending requests
- Processing flag to prevent race conditions
- Promise chaining for FIFO ordering
- Timer-based rate limit enforcement

## Implementation
```javascript
const createRateLimiter = (limit, interval) => {
  const queue = [];
  let processing = false;
  let lastRequest = 0;

  return async (request) => {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      queue.push({ request, resolve, reject });
      processQueue();
    });
  };

  async function processQueue() {
    if (processing || queue.length === 0) return;
    processing = true;

    const now = Date.now();
    const timeSinceLastRequest = now - lastRequest;
    const delay = timeSinceLastRequest < interval ? interval - timeSinceLastRequest : 0;

    setTimeout(async () => {
      const { request, resolve, reject } = queue.shift();
      lastRequest = Date.now();

      try {
        const result = await request();
        resolve(result);
      } catch (error) {
        reject(error);
      }

      processing = false;
      processQueue();
    }, delay);
  }
};
```

## Benefits
- Maintains request order through FIFO queue
- Prevents rate limit violations with timing control
- Handles concurrent requests gracefully

