// Route splitting
const Dashboard = React.lazy(() => import('./Dashboard'));

// Component splitting with chunk naming
const Chart = React.lazy(() => 
  import(/* webpackChunkName: "chart" */ './Chart')
);

// Webpack splitChunks config
optimization: {
  splitChunks: {
    chunks: 'all',
    vendor: {
      test: /[\\/]node_modules[\\/]/,
      name: 'vendors',
      chunks: 'all'
    }
  }
}
```

**Key Metrics to Track:**
- First Contentful Paint (FCP)
- Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)
- Time to Interactive (TTI)
- Bundle size reduction percentages
- Cache hit ratios

## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design performance-sensitive React architectures handling high-frequency data, including state shaping, rendering discipline, and UX consistency under load.

## Key Concepts

- Memoized selectors and reselect
- Data virtualization (react-window) for large series
